    <etym xml:lang="ru">Семантика слова недостаточно ясна; значение ‘тайный’, которое
        устанавливается на основании выражения %iaivæj%i ‘по секрету’, кажется нам исходным
        (‘тайный’ → ‘таинственный’ → ‘чудесный’ → ‘прекрасный’). В этом случае источником
        осетинского слова можно считать <mentioned xml:lang=""
            ><lang/><w>ġaib</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w>ġāib</w><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ ایﺐ)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ
                ایﺐ)</note><gloss><q>секрет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>тайна</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>невидимый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>скрытый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>тайный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>неземной</q></gloss></mentioned>, и пр., <mentioned xml:lang="tr"
                ><lang/><w>gayb</w></mentioned> id. В начале мы ожидали бы в осетинском %iq%i
        (*%iqaiv%i); ср., однако, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_app"/> рядом с <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_qapp"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The semantics of the word is not clear enough; the meaning ‘secret’, that is
        specified on the basis of the expression %iaivæj%i ‘secretly’, seems to be original
        (‘secret’ → ‘mystic’ → ‘miraclous’ → ‘beautiful’). In this case, the source of the Ossetic
        word can be considered <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>ġaib</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang=""><w>ġāib</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ ایﺐ)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (ﻗیﺐ, ﻗ
            ایﺐ)</note><gloss><q>secret</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>mistery</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>unvisible</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>covert</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>secret (adj.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w/><gloss><q>ethereal</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc., <mentioned xml:lang="tr"
                ><lang/><w>gayb</w></mentioned> id. We would expect initial %iq%i in Ossetic
        (*%iqaiv%i); cf., however, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_app"/> and <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_qapp"/>.</etym>
